volume.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles Presents: Merdude

description:
Flying into Houston from Canda, Katchoo has been away for two months where David and an over excited Francine are waiting.  She left under mysterious circumstances and returns skinnier to find Francine with a broken arm and a few dress sizes larger. 
 
A private detective reports Katchoo's return to the mysterious Darcy Parker. 
 
In a flashback we see a younger Katchoo being schooled in the art of high-class escorting by someone called Emma in the back of a limo while sipping champaign.
name: I Dream of You

description:
Katchoo's dreams are uneasy as is her relationship with Francine who feels slighted that her best friend could leave without explanation and still refuses to come clean about what happened in Canada.  
 
During her absence David has gotten Katchoo an art show at the local gallery and has her art on display without her knowledge. Katchoo breaks down and confesses to David some of her secret past and family breakdown she has kept from Francine. She tells him how Emma, now dying of AIDs, saved her from the gutter in LA and gave her a job as a high-class call girl.
 
Meanwhile Darcy Parker demands more diligent work from the P.I. she placed on Katchoo having lost her once already.
name: Someone to Watch Over Me

description:
David is still hanging around and his profession of love enrages a fragile Katchoo but his simple charm leads her to lightly kiss him much to the surprise of Francine. 
  
A call from the home in Canada where Emma is sends Katchoo to the airport again much to Francine's frustration at her friends secretive life. In Canada Katchoo confesses that she has feelings for David to Emma. As it starts to snow Emma passes-away.  
 
David and Francine arrive at the home and wait for their friend unannounced.
name: Echoes of Home

description:
An impatient Darcy Parker sends Tambi to give the P.I. some encouragement. 
 
Katchoo's mood has lightened and she is much more her playful self once again which soon changes when Francine's mother and uncle Maury come to stay. 
 
Darcy flies into Houston and is met by Veronica to take care of business personally.
name: Guess Who's Coming to Dinner

description:
Katchoo's dreams are still uneasy and the ghost of Emma looms large in her subconscious. She finally takes a call from David and buries herself in her artworks.
 
Francie has a bad day bumping into Freddie and fiancee, the bubbly and lithe, Casey. Feeling inadequate she buys a more sexy dress much to Katchoo's surprise and delight. 
 
Meanwhile a badly beaten Digman is left at a hospital where his facial injuries remind Detective Walsh of how Katchoo handled herself when she was in custody, giving him cause to issue a warrant for her arrest for questioning.
name: Something I Can't Hear

description:
Francine's dreams about her two best friends and wakes to find that she is in love with David. The police arrive to arrest Katchoo much to Francine's distress and disbelief.
 
Darcy Parker's organisation shows signs of decent as Samantha and Tambi conspire against her wishes. Tambi goes on a mission to collect Katchoo.
name: Tic Toc

description:
With the arrest warrant hanging over her Francine is frustrated with David that Katchoo seemingly confides more in him than her.  
  
David makes a mistake and reveals that he knows more than he should when he tells Francine whats been going on with her best friend.
  
Darcy Parker's rage at her staff starts to get out of control and Detective Walsh starts putting the pieces together surrounding Katchoo and the the connections to Darcy.
name: I Talk to the Wind

description:
Samantha reveals some more of Katchoo's history with the Parker Girls as she and Bambi take Francine and David hostage. 
 
Detective Walsh receives a call from Katchoo giving him insight into the situation. When Katchoo arrives back at the house she finds Darcy toying with a restrained Francine and goes onto to reveal Davids secret identity.  
 
Katchoo betrays Samantha to an obviously out of control Darcy. Walsh arrives a gun battle ensues and blood is shed.
name: Do You Remember Yesterdays?

description:
As Katchoo recovers her dreams are of Emma and more settled. Walsh reveals that Bambi Baker is going to jail for the killing of Digman. Walsh also gives Katchoo her FBI file, the contents of which both surprise and embarrass her.
                                                                                                                                  
Freddie meets up with Chuck and during a conversation he finds he still loves Francine. 
                                                                                                                                 
David shows up at the hospital and is cold shouldered by the girls. He reveals he is just an art student and doesn't even work for Darcy, he just  did her a favor by following Katchoo. By way of payment David asked Darcy for the beach hut in Hawaii where Katchoo and Emma stayed and he gifts it to Katchoo by way of an apology.  
                                                                                                                                   
Tambi arrives in Houston.
name: A Good Night's Sleep

description:
Back at home the girls are being evicted and Freddie's obsession with Francine is beginning to consume him. Casey is frustrated with Freddie's lack of passion with her. 
 
Francine bumps into Margie who might be able to help with their housing problem but is somewhat shocked to find that people think she and Katchoo are a couple. 
 
Francine and Katchoo's first kiss is interrupted by a knock at the door.
name: The Homecoming

description:
Freddie obtains some sexy photographs and a string bikini of Francine's from her Ex Chuck after a strange encounter with Chucks new girlfriend.
                                                                                                                                  
David professes his love for Katchoo once more and despite her anger she agrees to be with him, leaving Francine confused and dismayed.  
                                                                                                                                    
Katchoo lets David think they slept together but David's dreams reveal he still has secrets.
name: Queen of Hearts

description:
Freddie's doubts about his forthcoming marriage grow and he confronts Francine about their relationship. 
 
In a dream/flashback David recalls meeting a very drunk Katchoo at a party of Darcy's and being smitten only to find shes a working girl and involved with Darcy herself. 
 
Francine decides to run away and leave her friends to their new life together and Katchoo decides she has to fix things.
name: Goodbye

description:
In one of her out-of-character moments Francine heads to Hawaii where she spies on soontobe-wed Freddie. Katchoo and David chase after her to bring her home before she can crash the wedding and do something she will regret. 
 
On the flight over David has his chair repeated kicked by a 9 year-old Bjork (according to the SIP Source book) 
  
Casey and Freddie have an awkward time, esp as Freddie keeps sensing/smelling things that remind him of Francine.
 
David catches a glimpse of the tattoo on Katchoo's breast and brings back some bad memories.
name: It's A Good Life

description:
Overview:

Find out what happens when superheroes take off their capes. Welcome to Common Grounds, the hero hangout and coffee-and-donut shop, where true tales of the human side of the superhuman get spilled every month. Some gut-wrenching, some funny, but all told from the heart by new writing sensation Troy Hickman. Two stories every month! In this issue, artist Dan Jurgens examines the downside of being the fastest man alive, while the Powers team of Oeming and Pantazis tread the dangerous ground of the superhero men’s room. Really
name: Beyond the Speed of Life / Head Games
Sanctuary / Heir of Truth
Time of Their Lives / Fat Chance / Glory Days
Where Monsters Dine! / Lovelife
This'll be the Day / Loose Ends

character_credits.name: The Man In The Iron Mask

first_appearance_characters.name: The Man In The Iron Mask

name: Earth Fights Invasion from Outer Space!

description:
Nyoka and the Wild Goose Chase, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is tied to a post and a fire has started at her feet.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka trips on a tree root and falls to the ground. A lion lunges for the girl as she cries for help.

Ch. 3 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is hit on the head with a pistol, knocking her unconscious. She is then thrown into a river with a fast current that will send her over a deadly waterfall.

The Giant JurgoBeast, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - The JurgoBeast closes in on Nyoka.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - With a weapon in hand and Nyoka's back to him, Jurgo thinks to himself that he will have to dispose of Nyoka.

Ch. 3 cliffhanger ending - The JurgoBeast seizes Nyoka and it's deadly fangs move to within inches of Nyoka's face.
name: Nyoka and the Wild Goose Chase, Nyoka and the Giant JurgoBeast

description: This issue has several stories, rather than one or two, so they are not divided into cliffhanger ending chapters.
name: Barbacosi Madness, In Egypt, Post Office Mystery, And the Ape-Man Strangler

description:
Death in the North Pole Jungle, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka's plane crashes at the North Pole, but she falls out of the plane before it crashes. When she awakens she sees several jungle animals and a huge ape with arms stretched out is looking at her. She screams and falls unconscious in the snow.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is gagged and tied to a post. A lion and what looks like a large white cougar approach her.

Nyoka and the Gazelle Boy, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is pushed out of a tall tree and she is heading toward the ground that is covered with rocks.
name: Death in the North Pole Jungle, Nyoka and the Gazelle Boy

description:
The Jungle Ranch of Jee-Raff Jed, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - The Black Bullet's men tie Nyoka to a large tree, including tying a rope tied so tightly around her neck so she cannot scream for help. Then the Black Bullet ties a knife to a rope hanging above Nyoka's head and spins the rope faster and faster, sending the blade ever closer to Nyoka's head.

Jungle Revenge, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - This cliffhanger is a close variation of the issue's cover and has to be one of the deadliest chapter endings ever for Nyoka. Trying to escape an alligator, Nyoka paddles away in her canoe, but falis to see a large piece of driftwood. When the canoe hits the driftwood, Nyoka is thrown into the air. Her head brutally hits the driftwood and she is knocked unconscious. The chapter ends with an unconscious Nyoka actually laying across the alligator's gaping jaws, with her hands and part of her head in the water! As the writer's commentary reads, "A snap of his massive jaws and it will be all over for Nyoka, the Jungle Girl".

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka and Little Tangi have their arms tied behind their backs. They are forced to lean down over the chopping block and the executioner raises his giant blade......
name: The Jungle Ranch of Jee-Raff Jed, Jungle Revenge

description:
Railroad of Death, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Simon DeGree gags Nyoka and then securely ties her arms behind her back with rope, plus tying her ankles together. He then ties her to a set of railroad tracks by connecting rope around her neck to the railroad track.

The Strange Hunt, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - A moat filled with alligators threatens Nyoka.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A drawbridges raises up and Nyoka falls back, apparently into the clutches of Count Meout.
name: Railroad of Death, The Strange Hunt

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Only an indirect cliffhanger here, as the apparent leader of the Leopard Men asks for volunteers to silence Nyoka.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - After almost choking to death from a vine that was wrapped around her neck, Nyoka is in a weakened state. Suddenly one of the Leopard Men leaps at the helpless girl.
name: The Human Leopards

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Narsty hits Nyoka on the head with his fist, knocking her out cold. Then he takes the unconscious girl to Poison Creek to make her drink the deadly water.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Fireblood and Nyoka have a long fight. Nyoka tries to jump on top of Fireblood, but he rolls out of the way, sending Nyoka crashing into a giant boulder. He then takes the unconscious girl and lays her next to a dead tiger, knowing that many hungry animals will soon be drawn to the scene.
name: The Sacred Goat of Kristan

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - This is a very rare instance in this series in which the cliffhanger does not include Nyoka. As a panther is about to jump on young Peter Pippingworth, the boy backs up to the edge of a cliff and suddenly finds himself falling off the cliff...

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - After Vic knocks Nyoka out by hitting her with the butt of his rifle, Blimey ties her up with rope. Then he puts a torch close to Nyoka and says that when the fire burns itself out, the leopard will return and take care of her. Soon the leopard does return and Nyoka says, "Once that torch burns out I'm a goner. That leopard is gaining courage by the second!"
name: The Perils of Peter Pippingworth

description: Revenge of the River God, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Dench throws his shovel at Nyoka and it hits her squarely in the back, knocking the girl unconscious. Dench lays her on the ground, while Driscoll sharpens his large knife. Driscoll then leans over Nyoka and is about to cut off her head with his knife.....
name: Revenge of the River God, The Missing Heads

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - A spear thrown by a native is headed right for Nyoka's neck.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is trapped against a stone wall, unable to move, and a lion is closing in her.
name: Buried Terror

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka finds herself being swallowed alive by a stone monster.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka and Eloise have their arms tied behind their backs and then they are thrown into a deep pit where a giant gorilla awaits them.

Note: Don Winslow and Singapore Sal appear in single promo scenes only at the end of Nyoka's story and are not part of any story in this issue. Captain Tootsie does have a complete one page story.
name: The Weird Monsters

description:
The Dangerous Return, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Snark knocks Nyoka out by hitting her on the head with his gun. His partner, Boojum, tells him to get rid of her. Snark carries the unconscious girl to the edge of the ship and then he throws Nyoka into the raging waters of the ocean. As the writer puts it, "No human can remain long in the swirling sea off the Jungle Island of Doom."

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Two headhunter natives seize Nyoka, each holding one of Nyoka's arms. They plan to behead her!

Adventure in Burma, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Three of the Maharaja's men have Nyoka and Larry Grayson trapped against the wall, as they raise their swords to kill them.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is on a ladder that leads into a deep well. The Maharaja orders one of his men to set the ladder on fire. Swiftly the ladder is engulfed in flames and the fire encircles Nyoka, even spreading to her clothes!

Note: This photo cover of Clayton Moore and Kay Aldridge comes from a scene in the Republic Serial, The Perils of Nyoka, aka Nyoka and the Tigermen.
name: The Dangerous Return, Adventure in Burma

description:
The Treasure of Tiger's paw, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - A sniper shoots his rifle and the shot snaps Nyoka's canoe in two.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A rifle is aimed directly at Nyoka and the trigger is about to be squeezed.

The Flying Tiger, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka's old nemesis,Dr. Zanzere, knocks her out by hitting the back of her head with his gun. He is about to finish her by letting a tiger loose on her, but instead he and his partner flee and they take Nyoka with them. They escape on their flying tiger and when they get high in the air, Dr. Zanzere pushes Nyoka off, sending her falling helplessly downward....
name: The Treasure of Tiger's Paw, The Flying Tiger

description:
The Treacherous Game Hunt, Ch. 1 cliffhanger - Nyoka is being chased by a lion and she fails to see an animal trap prepared by her fiancee, Larry Grayson. Suddenly a net wraps itself around Nyoka and she is helpless as the lion approaches...

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Prowler hides on the ground near Nyoka and when he grabs her ankles and pulls, Nyoka smashes to the ground. Nyoka is stunned long enough for Prowler to tie her arms behind her back. Then he ties Nyoka to a tree and lets large game animals out of their cages. A lion, an leopard and two panthers are all headed for the bound girl....

The Death Stalked Expedition, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Gread smashes the butt of his rifle into Nyoka's face, knocking her out cold. His partner, Hoag, tells him to simply shoot her, but Gread tells Hoag that the natives might hear a shot and that such is not necessary, as his rope will do the trick. He ties the knots in such a way that if the girl tries to escape she will strangle herself and if she does not, she will starve to death. The writer's words are probably the most chilling to date for a cliffhanger chapter ending for Nyoka. "Poor Nyoka! No matter what she does, she's doomed to die! If she tries to free herself, it means strangulation! If she doesn't, it means slow starvation!"
name: The Treacherous Game Hunt, The Death-Stalked Expedition

description:
The Human Statues of the Jungle, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka tries to sail over a river with the help of a vine, but the vine breaks and she falls down in the middle of the river. Suddenly four alligators have her trapped and are closing in on her from every direction!

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is running hard and she fails to notice that she is nearing the cliff's edge. All of a sudden it is too late and her feet go over the edge of the cliff and screams "Help!"

The Legendary Jungle Bird, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is trapped against a giant statue and natives with spears decree that she must die!
name: The Human Statues of the Jungle, The Legendary Jungle Bird

description:
The Lost Civilization, Ch.1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka find herself in the unbreakable grip of a caveman and he is pulling her away. She thinks that Larry Grayson will soon come to save her, but he lying is unconscious at the base of Jungle Mountain.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is being chased by cavemen. She thinks she sees a way to escape, so she starts down the mountain by clinging to a vine. However, the cavemen do not need to chase her. They tip over a huge bin of hot liquid, in an effort to scald the girl to death! Nyoka says aloud, "There's nowhere to move! There's nothing I can do!" The writer sums it up with this chilling commentary: "Nyoka may have discovered a lost civilization, but in doing so, it looks as if she has lost her life!"

The Jungle Rythms of Death, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Natives with spears are chasing Nyoka, Larry Grayson and Peter Pizzicatto.
name: The Lost Civilization, The Jungle Rythms of Death

description:
Fury on the Wing, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - A stampede of horses are chasing Nyoka. Looking back at them while running, she trips on a rock and falls to the ground. It will only be a matter of seconds now before the horses reach her and crush her with their deadly hooves!

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A group of at least seven natives with spears are aiming them at Nyoka and ready to throw them...

The Petrified Jungle, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Billows knocks Nyoka out by hitting her on the head with the end of his rifle. Crandall so thoroughly ties her arms and legs that the girl cannot possibly escape. Then they throw her into a pond.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A jungle earthquake releases deadly fumes into the air near Nyoka and Billows. Nyoka believes that it is these fumes which petrified Ajax and Crandall who are standing frozen nearby.
name: Fury on the Wing, The Petrified Jungle

description:
Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Before Nyoka can react, Craggly turns around and hits her on the head with his gun, knocking the girl out cold. He then leaves meat on the ground next to her , knowing that the wild animals on the island will be attracted to the smell of the meat and will finish off Nyoka.

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A plane flying over the island where Nyoka and Craggly are trapped drops an atomic bomb...
name: The Isle of Nowhere
The Diamond of Death ; The Voo Doo Curse
